result.name: Coco Espresso

reviews.text: Nice and quiet coffee bar around Central. An experience which is different from the chain stores, and a lot more personal. High chairs all around and rather limited space for seating or on the table, but definitely a great place to visit for a casual meeting and quick catch up. One string benefit is that it is a lot quieter than other coffee shops as well.
My go to place for coffee whenever I am in Central. Just love sitting by the window and enjoy my cuppa coffee.

I had some nice coffee and cake here. It wasn't quite as good as the Cupping Room coffee from down the road, but it didn't stop me enjoying it. The cafe itself looks like a nice place to hang out. They also had some interesting bottled craft beer near the back.

Has got to be hands down the best coffee I've ever had. 

Sad it just had to be in a different country! 

The temperature as it is delivered to you is always just right and instantly drinkable. 

The blend of coffee is more of a soft mild roast. 

Staff knows a bit of English which is nice.
Good baristas, coffee could be a bit hotter,  service is more or less fast
